  "pr_number": 28335,
  "issue_number": 28039,
  "issue_title": "New sympy.physics.quantum.TensorProduct representation string is less readable",
  "issue_body": "Consider the following code:\n```\nfrom sympy.physics.quantum import Ket, TensorProduct\n\na = Ket('a')\nb = Ket('b')\n\nprint(TensorProduct(a, b))\n```\n\nPreviously ``a*b`` was possible, which would give `|a>*|b>`. Now that the star operator is deprecated, it is `|a>x|b>`. Is the extra x necessary? Especially for expressions with more Kets, this can quickly deteriorate the readibility of these expressions.\n\n",
  "merged_at": "2025-09-01T10:58:04Z",
